<subSubSection id="4FFD6520FFB4FFE2D0ECF98B7C13F947" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="075836ABFFB4FFE2D0ECF98B7C13F947" blockId="10.[151,1437,837,1763]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D0ECF98B7933F98B" bold="true" box="[199,315,1557,1583]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB4FFE2D248F98B7ADCF98B" authorityName="Shen &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[611,724,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lui">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D248F98B7ADCF98B" box="[611,724,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Balala lui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a broad and flat aedeagus with lateral subapical processes, but it differs in the following characteristics: 1) 
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB4FFE2D32FF9A47B4AF9F7" authorityName="Shen &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[772,834,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lui">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D32FF9A47B4AF9F7" box="[772,834,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">B. lui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a strong median longitudinal ridge through entire aedeagal shaft but this species lacks such a ridge; 2) the gonopore of this species is small and apical but that of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB4FFE2D54BF9C07D95F9D3" authorityName="Shen &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[1376,1437,1629,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lui">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D54BF9C07D95F9D3" box="[1376,1437,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">B. lui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is truncate and subapical on the ventral surface; 3) this species has the aedeagal shaft in front of the lateral process slender and gradually tapered but in 
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB4FFE2D21EF9387A7BF91B" authorityName="Shen &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[565,627,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lui">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D21EF9387A7BF91B" box="[565,627,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">B. lui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shaft in front of lateral process is broad and sharply tapered; and 4) the lateral process of this species is short and blunt but that of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E74D28FFB4FFE2D37AF9547B86F947" authorityName="Shen &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1995" box="[849,910,1737,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lui">
<emphasis id="3593EAB9FFB4FFE2D37AF9547B86F947" box="[849,910,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">B. lui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is attenuate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
